com.yworks.yfiles.view

Class GraphObstacleProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.yworks.yfiles.view.GraphObstacleProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IObstacleProvider

    public class GraphObstacleProvider
extends Object
implements IObstacleProvider
    An implementation of the IObstacleProvider interface that uses the edges and nodes of an IGraph as obstacles.

    The BridgeManager then calculates bridges for edge paths that cross these obstacles.

    This class can be used to add bridge support via the BridgeManager to a rendered IGraph.

    See Also:
    BridgeManager.addObstacleProvider(IObstacleProvider), BridgeManager, IObstacleProvider

        protected IGraph getGraph(IRenderContext context)
        Helper method that retrieves the IGraph to use from the .context

        This implementation uses the ILookup.lookup(java.lang.Class) of the CanvasControl to query the IGraph implementation.

        Parameters:
        context - The context to retrieve the implementation from.
        Returns:
        The IGraph instance to query or null.

      • getObstacles

        public GeneralPath getObstacles(IRenderContext context)
        Iterates over all Edges and Nodes to query an IObstacleProvider from the IModelItem's ILookup.lookup(java.lang.Class).

        This method will depending on the EdgeQueryingEnabled and NodeQueryingEnabled property query the items for an implementation of IObstacleProvider and concatenate all resulting GeneralPath obstacles into one path that will then be returned.

        Specified by:
        getObstacles in interface IObstacleProvider
        Parameters:
        context - The context where the obstacles are queried for.
        Returns:
        A path that is the concatenated path of all obstacles for the given context.
